spanGrp.span: ‘We take this road to get to Buenos Aires.
Ji ñala rö sa shkö-glo dömĩũ-lo dia Buenos Aires ra
We go there a lot. Others come from El Carmen,
Sa jã/ sa mĩ-gẽu-lo-ra sa ĩã/ siga-wa kebiye ñayugẽsã' rö Carmen
those from Guanacaste, El Carmen, San Bisente wait for the bus at that crossing.
tsõ Guanakaste wa El Carmen wa San Bisente wa të bus kiskse-gẽ je kruse ska
They come down. Those from Guanacaste wait for it at their own crossing.
Bötömĩũ-lo-nẽ Guanakaste wa dömĩsãu-lo-nẽ të cha kiskse-mĩ í wakwa kruse ska
There is only onw road to get there.
Bötömĩũ-lo klë/ ñala de/ ñala dö-glö-mĩũ rö e-tka uñabö
Only up there is there a place uh…called Rancho,
solamente mãjuir (extra) kã' kie-ite-nã esteee Rancho ska bönẽ
where there is a crossing going to Olan;
je kruse mãu e-gla kruse mãu Olan wa
it goes all the way there
and gets to another crossing called Salitre-Ujarraz.
jeska otro kruse rö kie-gẽ-nẽ-ite rö nã Salitre jamẽ Ujarras
Jeska ñala mãu e-tka uñawajebö mãu e-gla mãu
which a bit further down gets to the clinic.
Jeska wagweta yenã mãu-nẽ (hmm) rö dömĩũ-nẽ rö klinika ska
There one goes down; that road goes straight into town, in the center.
Jeska e-gla bötöũ mãu-nẽ wagweta je nẽ mãu-nẽ ñawösiga damĩũ dia sentro sh (r) sh (r) shãnã
Form there you come to Rancho
(hm) Ta jeska ra bötöũ je (hm) dögaũ jeska (_) Rancho ska ra
again and then to Ujarraz. There is only one road.
Dögaũ ji Ujarras ska (_) ñala rö e-tka uñawajebö
No one gets lost there. You get to the big bridge;
Ka jeska yurö she-nã dömĩgaũ-nẽ puente keyege ska ra
there is the Santa María-Ujarraz crossing.
jeska nẽ kruse rö Santa Maria jamẽ Ujarras
From there you get here; no one gets lost.
Jeska bötöũ-mĩu-nẽ dömĩgaũ-nẽ jiska ka yurö she-nã
We walk like that; that is also ow people come here.
Jebi sa shkö-gẽ rö jebi pe dö-gẽ-te dö-gẽ-gaũ jiwa
Thus we go down there too.
Jebö ji ska sa mĩgẽu-lo-nẽ wak
male shkö-gẽ rö (hm) je tebeli_yaga inga
male shkö-gẽ rö í wakwa klö wa
and yet others go on horseback.’
